{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I was asked to come here and speak about creation."},{"time":3000,"text":"And I only have 15 minutes, and I see they're counting already."},{"time":7000,"text":"And I can -- in 15 minutes, I think I can touch only a very rather janitorial branch of creation,"},{"time":14000,"text":"which I call \"creativity.\""},{"time":17000,"text":"Creativity is how we cope with creation."},{"time":21000,"text":"While creation sometimes seems a bit un-graspable, or even pointless,"},{"time":27000,"text":"creativity is always meaningful."},{"time":30000,"text":"See, for instance, in this picture."},{"time":31000,"text":"You know, creation is what put that dog in that picture,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and creativity is what makes us see a chicken on his hindquarters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"When you think about -- you know, creativity has a lot to do with causality too."},{"time":46000,"text":"You know, when I was a teenager, I was a creator."},{"time":49000,"text":"I just did things."},{"time":52000,"text":"Then I became an adult and started knowing who I was,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and tried to maintain that persona -- I became creative."},{"time":58000,"text":"It wasn't until I actually did a book and a retrospective exhibition, that I could track exactly --"},{"time":66000,"text":"looks like all the craziest things that I had done, all my drinking, all my parties --"},{"time":70000,"text":"they followed a straight line that brings me to the point"},{"time":72000,"text":"that actually I'm talking to you at this moment."},{"time":74000,"text":"Though it's actually true, you know,"},{"time":78000,"text":"the reason I'm talking to you right now is because I was born in Brazil."},{"time":81000,"text":"If I was born in Monterey, probably would be in Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"You know, I was born in Brazil and grew up in the '70s"},{"time":89000,"text":"under a climate of political distress,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and I was forced to learn to communicate in a very specific way --"},{"time":96000,"text":"in a sort of a semiotic black market."},{"time":98000,"text":"You couldn't really say what you wanted to say;"},{"time":101000,"text":"you had to invent ways of doing it."},{"time":103000,"text":"You didn't trust information very much."},{"time":105000,"text":"That led me to another step of why I'm here today,"},{"time":108000,"text":"is because I really liked media of all kinds."},{"time":111000,"text":"I was a media junkie, and eventually got involved with advertising."},{"time":115000,"text":"My first job in Brazil"},{"time":117000,"text":"was actually to develop a way to improve the readability of billboards,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and based on speed, angle of approach and actually blocks of text."},{"time":126000,"text":"It was very -- actually, it was a very good study,"},{"time":129000,"text":"and got me a job in an ad agency."},{"time":131000,"text":"And they also decided that I had to --"},{"time":134000,"text":"to give me a very ugly Plexiglas trophy for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"And another point -- why I'm here --"},{"time":141000,"text":"is that the day I went to pick up the Plexiglas trophy,"},{"time":145000,"text":"I rented a tuxedo for the first time in my life,"},{"time":148000,"text":"picked the thing -- didn't have any friends."},{"time":150000,"text":"On my way out, I had to break a fight apart."},{"time":153000,"text":"Somebody was hitting somebody else with brass knuckles."},{"time":156000,"text":"They were in tuxedos, and fighting. It was very ugly."},{"time":158000,"text":"And also -- advertising people do that all the time -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":164000,"text":"and I -- well, what happened is when I went back, it was on the way back to my car,"},{"time":169000,"text":"the guy who got hit decided to grab a gun --"},{"time":171000,"text":"I don't know why he had a gun --"},{"time":173000,"text":"and shoot the first person he decided to be his aggressor."},{"time":175000,"text":"The first person was wearing a black tie, a tuxedo. It was me."},{"time":181000,"text":"Luckily, it wasn't fatal, as you can all see."},{"time":184000,"text":"And, even more luckily, the guy said that he was sorry"},{"time":189000,"text":"and I bribed him for compensation money, otherwise I press charges."},{"time":193000,"text":"And that's how -- with this money I paid for a ticket to come to the United States in 1983,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and that's very -- the basic reason I'm talking to you here today:"},{"time":203000,"text":"because I got shot. (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"Well, when I started working with my own work, I decided that I shouldn't do images."},{"time":214000,"text":"You know, I became -- I took this very iconoclastic approach."},{"time":218000,"text":"Because when I decided to go into advertising, I wanted to do --"},{"time":221000,"text":"I wanted to airbrush naked people on ice, for whiskey commercials,"},{"time":227000,"text":"that's what I really wanted to do. (Laughter)"},{"time":228000,"text":"But I -- they didn't let me do it, so I just -- you know,"},{"time":231000,"text":"they would only let me do other things."},{"time":233000,"text":"But I wasn't into selling whiskey; I was into selling ice."},{"time":237000,"text":"The first works were actually objects."},{"time":239000,"text":"It was kind of a mixture of found object, product design and advertising."},{"time":244000,"text":"And I called them relics."},{"time":246000,"text":"They were displayed first at Stux Gallery in 1983."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"This is the clown skull."},{"time":252000,"text":"Is a remnant of a race of -- a very evolved race of entertainers."},{"time":255000,"text":"They lived in Brazil, long time ago. (Laughter)"},{"time":259000,"text":"This is the Ashanti joystick."},{"time":261000,"text":"Unfortunately, it has become obsolete because it was designed for Atari platform."},{"time":266000,"text":"A Playstation II is in the works, maybe for the next TED I'll bring it."},{"time":271000,"text":"The rocking podium. (Laughter)"},{"time":276000,"text":"This is the pre-Columbian coffeemaker. (Laughter)"},{"time":281000,"text":"Actually, the idea came out of an argument that I had at Starbucks,"},{"time":285000,"text":"that I insisted that I wasn't having Colombian coffee;"},{"time":287000,"text":"the coffee was actually pre-Columbian."},{"time":289000,"text":"The Bonsai table."},{"time":295000,"text":"The entire Encyclopedia Britannica bound in a single volume, for travel purposes."},{"time":305000,"text":"And the half tombstone, for people who are not dead yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"I wanted to take that into the realm of images,"},{"time":314000,"text":"and I decided to make things that had the same identity conflicts."},{"time":319000,"text":"So I decided to do work with clouds."},{"time":321000,"text":"Because clouds can mean anything you want."},{"time":324000,"text":"But now I wanted to work in a very low-tech way,"},{"time":327000,"text":"so something that would mean at the same time"},{"time":330000,"text":"a lump of cotton, a cloud and Durer's praying hands --"},{"time":334000,"text":"although this looks a lot more like Mickey Mouse's praying hands."},{"time":338000,"text":"But I was still, you know -- this is a kitty cloud."},{"time":342000,"text":"They're called \"Equivalents,\" after Alfred Stieglitz's work."},{"time":347000,"text":"\"The Snail.\""},{"time":348000,"text":"But I was still working with sculpture,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and I was really trying to go flatter and flatter."},{"time":353000,"text":"\"The Teapot.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"I had a chance to go to Florence, in -- I think it was '94,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and I saw Ghiberti's \"Door of Paradise.\""},{"time":362000,"text":"And he did something that was very tricky."},{"time":365000,"text":"He put together two different media from different periods of time."},{"time":368000,"text":"First, he got an age-old way of making it, which was relief,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and he worked this with three-point perspective, which was brand-new technology at the time."},{"time":378000,"text":"And it's totally overkill."},{"time":381000,"text":"And your eye doesn't know which level to read."},{"time":383000,"text":"And you become trapped into this kind of representation."},{"time":386000,"text":"So I decided to make these very simple renderings,"},{"time":390000,"text":"that at first they are taken as a line drawing --"},{"time":393000,"text":"you know, something that's very -- and then I did it with wire."},{"time":397000,"text":"The idea was to -- because everybody overlooks white -- like pencil drawings, you know?"},{"time":403000,"text":"And they would look at it -- \"Ah, it's a pencil drawing.\""},{"time":405000,"text":"Then you have this double take and see that it's actually something that existed in time."},{"time":409000,"text":"It had a physicality,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and you start going deeper and deeper into sort of narrative"},{"time":415000,"text":"that goes this way, towards the image. So this is \"Monkey with Leica.\""},{"time":423000,"text":"\"Relaxation.\""},{"time":425000,"text":"\"Fiat Lux.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"And the same way the history of representation"},{"time":432000,"text":"evolved from line drawings to shaded drawings."},{"time":435000,"text":"And I wanted to deal with other subjects."},{"time":437000,"text":"I started taking that into the realm of landscape,"},{"time":440000,"text":"which is something that's almost a picture of nothing."},{"time":444000,"text":"I made these pictures called \"Pictures of Thread,\""},{"time":446000,"text":"and I named them after the amount of yards that I used to represent each picture."},{"time":450000,"text":"These always end up being a photograph at the end,"},{"time":452000,"text":"or more like an etching in this case."},{"time":454000,"text":"So this is a lighthouse."},{"time":461000,"text":"This is \"6,500 Yards,\" after Corot. \"9,000 Yards,\" after Gerhard Richter."},{"time":468000,"text":"And I don't know how many yards, after John Constable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"Departing from the lines, I decided to tackle the idea of points,"},{"time":477000,"text":"like which is more similar to the type of representation that we find in photographs themselves."},{"time":482000,"text":"I had met a group of children in the Caribbean island of Saint Kitts,"},{"time":486000,"text":"and I did work and play with them."},{"time":490000,"text":"I got some photographs from them."},{"time":492000,"text":"Upon my arrival in New York, I decided --"},{"time":494000,"text":"they were children of sugar plantation workers."},{"time":498000,"text":"And by manipulating sugar over a black paper, I made portraits of them."},{"time":503000,"text":"These are -- (Applause) --"},{"time":507000,"text":"Thank you. This is \"Valentina, the Fastest.\""},{"time":511000,"text":"It was just the name of the child,"},{"time":513000,"text":"with the little thing you get to know of somebody that you meet very briefly."},{"time":517000,"text":"\"Valicia.\""},{"time":521000,"text":"\"Jacynthe.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"But another layer of representation was still introduced."},{"time":527000,"text":"Because I was doing this while I was making these pictures,"},{"time":530000,"text":"I realized that I could add still another thing"},{"time":533000,"text":"I was trying to make a subject --"},{"time":535000,"text":"something that would interfere with the themes,"},{"time":540000,"text":"so chocolate is very good, because it has --"},{"time":544000,"text":"it brings to mind ideas that go from scatology to romance."},{"time":549000,"text":"And so I decided to make these pictures,"},{"time":552000,"text":"and they were very large, so you had to walk away from it to be able to see them."},{"time":555000,"text":"So they're called \"Pictures of Chocolate.\""},{"time":556000,"text":"Freud probably could explain chocolate better than I. He was the first subject."},{"time":561000,"text":"And Jackson Pollock also."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"Pictures of crowds are particularly interesting,"},{"time":569000,"text":"because, you know, you go to that --"},{"time":571000,"text":"you try to figure out the threshold with something you can define very easily,"},{"time":574000,"text":"like a face, goes into becoming just a texture."},{"time":578000,"text":"\"Paparazzi.\""},{"time":582000,"text":"I used the dust at the Whitney Museum to render some pieces of their collection."},{"time":586000,"text":"And I picked minimalist pieces because they're about specificity."},{"time":590000,"text":"And you render this with the most non-specific material,"},{"time":593000,"text":"which is dust itself."},{"time":595000,"text":"Like, you know, you have the skin particles of every single museum visitor."},{"time":599000,"text":"They do a DNA scan of this, they will come up with a great mailing list."},{"time":605000,"text":"This is Richard Serra."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"I bought a computer, and [they] told me it had millions of colors in it."},{"time":617000,"text":"You know an artist's first response to this is, who counted it? You know?"},{"time":621000,"text":"And I realized that I never worked with color,"},{"time":624000,"text":"because I had a hard time controlling the idea of single colors."},{"time":628000,"text":"But once they're applied to numeric structure,"},{"time":631000,"text":"then you can feel more comfortable."},{"time":633000,"text":"So the first time I worked with colors was by making these mosaics of Pantone swatches."},{"time":638000,"text":"They end up being very large pictures,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and I photographed with a very large camera --"},{"time":642000,"text":"an 8x10 camera."},{"time":644000,"text":"So you can see the surface of every single swatch --"},{"time":646000,"text":"like in this picture of Chuck Close."},{"time":648000,"text":"And you have to walk very far to be able to see it."},{"time":653000,"text":"Also, the reference to Gerhard Richter's use of color charts --"},{"time":660000,"text":"and the idea also entering another realm of representation that's very common to us today,"},{"time":664000,"text":"which is the bit map."},{"time":666000,"text":"I ended up narrowing the subject to Monet's \"Haystacks.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"This is something I used to do as a joke --"},{"time":673000,"text":"you know, make -- the same like -- Robert Smithson's \"Spiral Jetty\" --"},{"time":678000,"text":"and then leaving traces, as if it was done on a tabletop."},{"time":682000,"text":"I tried to prove that he didn't do that thing in the Salt Lake."},{"time":686000,"text":"But then, just doing the models, I was trying to explore the relationship"},{"time":690000,"text":"between the model and the original."},{"time":692000,"text":"And I felt that I would have to actually go there and make some earthworks myself."},{"time":698000,"text":"I opt for very simple line drawings -- kind of stupid looking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"And at the same time, I was doing these very large constructions,"},{"time":706000,"text":"being 150 meters away."},{"time":709000,"text":"Now I would do very small ones, which would be like --"},{"time":713000,"text":"but under the same light, and I would show them together,"},{"time":716000,"text":"so the viewer would have to really figure it out what one he was looking."},{"time":719000,"text":"I wasn't interested in the very large things, or in the small things."},{"time":722000,"text":"I was more interested in the things in between,"},{"time":725000,"text":"you know, because you can leave an enormous range for ambiguity there."},{"time":731000,"text":"This is like you see -- the size of a person over there."},{"time":736000,"text":"This is a pipe."},{"time":741000,"text":"A hanger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743000,"text":"And this is another thing that I did -- you know working"},{"time":748000,"text":"-- everybody loves to watch somebody draw,"},{"time":750000,"text":"but not many people have a chance to watch somebody draw in --"},{"time":753000,"text":"a lot of people at the same time, to evidence a single drawing."},{"time":757000,"text":"And I love this work,"},{"time":760000,"text":"because I did these cartoonish clouds over Manhattan for a period of two months."},{"time":765000,"text":"And it was quite wonderful, because I had an interest -- an early interest -- in theater,"},{"time":769000,"text":"that's justified on this thing."},{"time":771000,"text":"In theater, you have the character and the actor in the same place,"},{"time":775000,"text":"trying to negotiate each other in front of an audience."},{"time":777000,"text":"And in this, you'd have like a --"},{"time":779000,"text":"something that looks like a cloud, and it is a cloud at the same time."},{"time":783000,"text":"So they're like perfect actors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786000,"text":"My interest in acting, especially bad acting, goes a long way."},{"time":792000,"text":"Actually, I once paid like 60 dollars"},{"time":794000,"text":"to see a very great actor to do a version of \"King Lear,\""},{"time":798000,"text":"and I felt really robbed, because by the time the actor started being King Lear,"},{"time":803000,"text":"he stopped being the great actor that I had paid money to see."},{"time":806000,"text":"On the other hand, you know, I paid like three dollars, I think --"},{"time":814000,"text":"and I went to a warehouse in Queens"},{"time":816000,"text":"to see a version of \"Othello\" by an amateur group."},{"time":821000,"text":"And it was quite fascinating, because you know the guy --"},{"time":824000,"text":"his name was Joey Grimaldi --"},{"time":826000,"text":"he impersonated the Moorish general"},{"time":829000,"text":"-- you know, for the first three minutes he was really that general,"},{"time":831000,"text":"and then he went back into plumber, he worked as a plumber, so --"},{"time":835000,"text":"plumber, general, plumber, general --"},{"time":838000,"text":"so for three dollars, I saw two tragedies for the price of one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844000,"text":"See, I think it's not really about impression,"},{"time":849000,"text":"making people fall for a really perfect illusion,"},{"time":851000,"text":"as much as it is to make -- I usually work at the lowest threshold of visual illusion."},{"time":857000,"text":"Because it's not about fooling somebody,"},{"time":860000,"text":"it's actually giving somebody a measure of their own belief:"},{"time":863000,"text":"how much you want to be fooled."},{"time":865000,"text":"That's why we pay to go to magic shows and things like that."},{"time":869000,"text":"Well, I think that's it."},{"time":871000,"text":"My time is nearly up."},{"time":872000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}